Description.LocalizedString: It shambled along, unstopping, powered by something dark and unknowable.
Even in the dark of night, its body glistened with gold.
The leaves have long since fallen and left a chilling silhouette.
Now armed with four legs, it could knock out its prey before destroying them.
The flesh mixed with the flora, turning to something like stone.
Despite the enormous damage its body took, it lurched ever forward, unfeeling.
The filth of the outdoors infected the flesh that remained.
Whatever animates this abomination continues to do so, even after the skin and sinew have sloughed away.
Atop the dreadful pile of childrenâ€™s toys sat the most hideous piece of all.
A mask they found themselves wearing at the masquerade ball.
It doesnâ€™t look like itâ€™s going to melt any time soon.
With its new appearance, The Dredge was sure to attract more prey.
After decimating the people of The Garden, it began to become one with The Garden.
To look upon its horrifying visage is to see beyond the limits of what human flesh could take.
Severed from anything resembling actual life, it turned into a putrid mess.
No eyes remain in its sockets, but this skull still scans its environment, hungry for prey.
The doll parts formed something almost resembling a human hand.
Whatever force embellished it with gold turned the end of its arm into a beautiful but deadly blade.
The ornaments arenâ€™t the only things that will be hung with care.
The rusty nails coming out of its hooves could easily pierce the skin.
Hands that once tended to The Garden now grew green themselves.
Hardened by the growth of scar tissue, it struck harder than ever.
The corruption reached through all of its extremities, turning it as foul as it was dangerous.
Stiff and cold, its horrifying limb smashes and strikes harder than ever.
